Problem Statement:

Currently, there is no visibility into the operational status of regional segments. This lack of information makes it difficult to understand which segments are actively being used and which are obsolete. This can lead to inefficiencies in resource allocation, data management, and reporting.

Technical Solution:

Introduce a "Regional Segment Status" field:
Add a new field to the regional segment entity with the following possible values: "Active" and "Retired."
Automated Status Derivation:
Implement a logic that automatically determines the segment status based on the status of its associated lines of business.
If at least one associated line of business is "Active," the regional segment status should be set to "Active."
If all associated lines of business are "Retired" or do not exist, the regional segment status should be set to "Retired."
Data Persistence:
Ensure the "Regional Segment Status" is persisted in the database.
User Interface (UI) Display:
Display the "Regional Segment Status" in the regional segment details view within the user interface.
Data Synchronization:
Ensure that when the line of business status is updated, that the regional segment status is also updated.
